The paper deals with differential privacy, which is a topic in computer science that falls under several sub-categories. The focus on selecting the k items of highest quality out of a set of d items suggests that the paper is related to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of differentially private algorithms also suggests that the paper may be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the use of lower bounds suggests that the paper may be related to complexity theory (cs.CC).
